# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. Restart `npm run dev` after changes.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS credentials (optional when running under an IAM role with the required
# DynamoDB + S3 permissions). Falls back to the default AWS SDK credential
# provider chain when unset.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AMPERE_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor session signing secret. Used to sign/verify editor postMessage
# payloads between the CMS shell and the preview iframe when running against
# a cross-origin preview host (not required for same-origin development).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_STUDIO_EDITOR_SECRET=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Active client id. Used as the DynamoDB partition key for every per-client
# query (products, categories, images, submissions, editor cache) and shown
# in the sidebar. Defaults to "ampere" when unset. Will eventually come from
# the authenticated user's Cognito profile instead.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_DEFAULT_CLIENT_ID=ampere

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub editor access. For the MVP, Ampere Studio uses one server-side token
# and one hardcoded repo/branch until Cognito client metadata is added.
#
# Create a GitHub PAT with access to the repo and Contents read/write.
# Classic PAT: `repo` scope.
# Fine-grained PAT: selected repos, Contents read/write, Metadata read-only.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_GITHUB_TOKEN=
# AMPERE_DEFAULT_REPO=owner/repository
# AMPERE_DEFAULT_REF=main
# AMPERE_DEFAULT_SITE_URL=https://example.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS SES — used to send order shipment notifications and receipts.
# The sender address must be verified in SES (production: out of sandbox).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_SES_SENDER_EMAIL=noreply@amperecreativegroup.com
# AMPERE_SES_REGION=us-east-2

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ampere Studio URL — used in dev invite emails when the request origin is
# unavailable (e.g. server-side rendering). Defaults to localhost in dev.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AMPERE_STUDIO_URL=http://localhost:3000
